    "body": "Hi @rossant ,\n\nI don't think this is a problem with the widgets.  Instead its an intentional behavior of browsers with canvas elements.  I've whipped up a [jsfiddle illustrating the behavior](http://jsfiddle.net/2tQxV/1/).  All you need to do is set the tabindex of the canvas so the browser knows it can accept input.  \n\nAdding something like this \n\n``` javascript\n    .attr('tabindex', '1')\n```\n\nto the jquery commands that create your canvas should do the trick.  Can you try this and report back?\n"
  },
